The delegation is at your discretion, Mr. President.

271
00:17:44,260 --> 00:17:46,490
有人支持你  或许是好事
It might be good for you to have some support.

272
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:49,550
她的在场会削弱我作为国务卿的权威
Her presence undermines my authority as Secretary of State.

273
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:53,980
凯茜  佩特罗夫非常固执  这你相信我
Cathy, Petrov is incredibly stubborn. Trust me, I know.

274
00:17:54,150 --> 00:17:56,930
你为什么不愿意用上所有的资源呢
Why wouldn't you wanna have every asset available to you?

275
00:17:57,550 --> 00:17:59,170
请允许我做这件事  总统先生
Allow me to do this, Mr. President.

276
00:17:59,170 --> 00:18:00,850
-先生  -如果能增加胜算
- Sir-- - If it increases our chances.

277
00:18:00,850 --> 00:18:02,710
会的  我保证
It will, I promise.

278
00:18:04,290 --> 00:18:07,070
那就一起吧  我们把简报过一遍
Then join us. We're going over the briefing now.

279
00:18:23,550 --> 00:18:25,010
你尽力了  弗兰克
You tried, Frank...

280
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:28,310
这已经比大多数人都强了
which is more than most people ever do.

281
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:31,300
现在  只剩下我们了
Right now, it's just us.

282
00:18:32,010 --> 00:18:33,400
闭上你的眼睛
Rest your eyes.

283
00:18:34,110 --> 00:18:36,430
我们有用不完的时间
We have all the time in the world.

284
00:18:44,110 --> 00:18:45,740
丹尼  发生什么事了
Danny, what was that?

